PWA, async jobs, channel manager, onboarding, and PRD-gap features

PWA + offline shell:
- Web manifest with shortcuts (Dashboard, Banking, Maintenance, Portal),
  Apple touch icon, maskable PNG icons (192/384/512), theme color.
- Service worker with network-first navigations, stale-while-revalidate
  for static assets, and a never-cache rule for /api and 3rd-party hosts.
- Install banner (Android Chrome beforeinstallprompt + iOS Add-to-Home-Screen
  hint) with 14-day dismiss memory.

Background jobs (BullMQ + Redis with graceful no-Redis fallback):
- QueueService that registers workers and enqueues with retries/backoff
  when REDIS_URL is set, runs handlers inline otherwise so the app keeps
  working in single-process deployments.
- Email sends, alert generation, Plaid sync, autopay, late fees, and
  channel sync now route through the queue with cron schedules
  (alerts hourly, autopay daily 9 UTC, late fees 9:15 UTC).

Channel manager (Airbnb/VRBO/Booking via iCal):
- ChannelFeed schema with bidirectional sync: import URLs pull bookings
  with cursorless poll; we generate per-feed export.ics tokens that other
  channels subscribe to so reservations cross-block automatically.
- Conflict detection on overlapping reservations from different feeds.

Onboarding:
- /onboarding/checklist endpoint that computes 8 setup steps
  (property, unit, tenant, bank/wallet, online pay, first payment,
  channel, first doc) with dynamic copy based on enabled integrations.
- Dashboard widget with progress bar + per-item CTAs, dismissible.

PRD gaps closed:
- Auto-pay (FR22): SetupIntent → off-session PaymentIntent recurring on
  tenant-chosen day-of-month, with Stripe customer + payment-method
  persistence and failure notifications.
- Late fee policy per lease (FR14): grace period, flat + percent (bps),
  applied idempotently by daily worker.
- Maintenance ratings (FR26) + technician scoring (FR72): tenant rates
  completed jobs 1–5; aggregate scores with avg rating, ratings count,
  and avg resolution hours.
- Property map view (FR4) endpoint with lat/lng + occupancy + open jobs
  for each active property.
- Property comparison (FR20) endpoint computing 12-month NOI, cap rate,
  and cash-on-cash for any set of property IDs.
- CSV exports (NFR26): transactions, rent roll, reservations.
- Audit log surfacing (NFR11): generic AuditService + read endpoint
  scoped to org via the user relation.
- Property knowledge base (FR5): WiFi, parking, utilities, appliance
  notes, emergency contacts, house rules, local recommendations.
- Guest portal (FR54): per-reservation guestToken backing a public
  /public/guest/:token endpoint that serves the welcome guide.
- Supply inventory (FR52): SupplyItem CRUD + qty adjust + shopping
  list (low-stock).
